title: Alabama Cycling Classic presents Sunny King Criterium
description: The Alabama Cycling Classic is proud to present the Sunny King Criterium.  The Alabama Cycling Classic is the first stop on USA Cycling's Professional National Calendar, and includes the Fort McClellan RR on Sunday for the Pro Men and Women.
course: The crit utilizes the same four corner course as previous editions of the event.
notes: USA Cycling rules for criterium racing apply.  Parking details will be released soon.

title: Alabama Cycling Classic Presents Fort McClellan RR
description: The Alabama Cycling Classic presents the Fort McClellan RR.  This event is the first event on the USA Cycling Professional National Calendar.  The road race will only feature the Pro/1 Men and Pro/1/2 Women in 2016.
course: Course features two challenging climbs, with the finish being on top of Bains Gap.  There is a techinical descent over the top of Bains Gap, so please make sure you have reviewed this before the race.
registration: Riders can pre-register at USA Cycling.
notes: USA Cycling rules for road races apply.  Parking and other race details will be added shortly.

title: AL State TT Championship
description: AL State TT.  This is the first year this race will serve as a qualifying event for the National Senior Games.  The Games will be in Birmingham in 2017.
course: There are four different course options this year, with two serving the 5 and 10K qualifying distance for Senior Games, and the other serving as the USA Cycling State Championship distance.   The courses are the same as years past, and are rolling courses.
notes:
Start times will be emailed to all participants, and posted on the event Facebook page on Friday morning.  

Start order for this year will be based on the distances as follows: 5K, 10K, 13.8 miles, and 23 miles.

Merckx category requires a mass start legal bike, and cannot utilize any of the following equipment: aerobars, disc wheel, rim depth deeper than 44 mm, aero helmet, and shoe covers.

Junior gear restrictions are in effect, and juniors will be required to roll out immediately after their run is completed.

Riders who enter multiple categories will make two runs.  We will do our best to accommodate riders to give them a break between start times, but it is not always possible.

title: AL State RR Championship
description:
Alabama State Road Race Championship.  The race this year features a new, rolling course that should be very fast.  

Also new this year is a registration refund for riders who volunteer to work the event at some point, or provide someone to assist with volunteering.  There will be a partial entry fee refund once they show up on-site to work.  Email me at slamp@usacycling.org if interested in assisting, or providing someone to assist.
course:
The race course, with elevation profile, can be found at the following link: https://ridewithgps.com/routes/15167795.

The start will be at the intersection of Pines Rd, and Beavers Rd.  You will ride from the parking area for a short distance on Hwy 31, then turn left onto Pines Rd to proceed to the course.
registration:
Online registration is on USA Cycling.  This event will be PRE-REG ONLY due to internet connectivity issues at the race venue.  You have until Thursday night at 11 PM to register!

Riders who qualify to do an additional race can purchase a second race for $10.  

All riders are required to have a USA Cycling license.  A one-day license is $10, but you will not be eligible for the championship on a one-day.  The only categories offered at this event eligible for the one-day are Male Cat 5, Female Cat 4, and the Junior races.
notes:
All categories listed are state championship categories.  Only riders who have a USA Cycling annual license, and are listed as a resident of AL are eligible for the state medals.  

Winners of the championship will be able to purchase a state championship jersey, and will receive instructions after the event on how to purchase this.

Wheel trucks will be provided, but you will need to bring your own spare wheels to put in the truck.  

Junior gear restrictions are in effect per USA Cycling rules.  Center line rule will be in effect, and will be strictly enforced.  If needed, we may pull riders who are out of contention, but give you a placing to ensure that we keep the roads clear.  This is for your safety, and will only be done if needed due to excess traffic on the course.
directions:
Parking is at Husky Park in Florette at the following address:
61 Florette Park Rd, Somerville, AL 35670

You will park here, and ride a short distance to the actual race course.

title: Alabama Wheelmen Grand Prix p/b Alabama Ear Institute
Gears and Beers Mobile - 2016
description:
Join the Delta Bike Project as we ride the streets of Mobile along some familiar, and not-so-familiar routes to raise money for more Fixit Stations and Bike Racks in Mobile. Last year we supported 280 riders for our first major fundraiser. 

The Purpose: 
100% of proceeds from Gears and Beers will go towards three things:
1. A large public bicycle parking corral with the location yet to be determined.
2. Four more DERO Fixit Stations and Pumps
3. Supporting DBP Programs (Time is Money Program, Read-to-Ride, Build a Bike Program, Education Classes, and support participation in other Community Projects)
course:
Fat Tire Ride (10 mi): https://www.strava.com/routes/6245004
